svg.title: A map showing the arrangement of the Vicarâ€™s study: a door enters on the lower left of the oblong room. On the shorter left-hand wall is a fireplace, surrounded by a sofa, two armchairs, and a side table with a lamp; beside the side table is a window on the wall opposite the door. Beside the window to the right is a tall stand with a pot on it, to the right of that a side chair, and the writing-table is in the upper right corner, sitting diagonally. Beside it on the shorter right-hand wall is a bookshelf, and a tallboy chest of drawers is in the lower right corner. Between the tallboy and the door are two side chairs.
